[![](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/11/concurso.jpg)](https://globalvoicesonline.org/wp-
content/uploads/2010/11/concurso.jpg)The 4th International online short film
contest for Responsible Consumption Culture [has its
winner](http://www.consumoresponsable.org/concursoconsumo/). [This
contest](http://www.ecodes.org/notas-de-prensa/4o-concurso-internacional-
online-de-cortos-por-el-consumo-responsable), organized by [ECODES
](http://www.ecodes.org/)and the General Direction of Consumption for the
Government of Aragon, called for entries in Spanish from short film producers
from Spain and Latin America. A Colombian short was selected as the winner
from the [10 international
finalists](http://www.consumoresponsable.org/concursoconsumo/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=67&Itemid=16).

The 10 finalists were from different regions of Spain, Brazil and Colombia.
Following, [the winning video](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j-dPF31dc-o):
_The Recicleta_ shows how not living within our ecological means can result in
drastic but necessary actions.

These next videos were some of the other finalistsâ€™ entries. This next video
is titled[ _Plastic_ ](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lz2F1VZYmz4)and comes
from Zaragoza, Spain. It playfully shows us how the simple plastic shopping
sac can take over our home. In an apartment we can take our bags elsewhere,
but on the planet, we can't move them out anywhere else:

From Brazil, [_Individual Choice_](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ofJZ1Y-TqjE)
was also running for the award. It shows how all the decisions we make on a
daily basis can be improved or changed to be more environmentally responsible:

You can view the rest of the videos and learn more about the concepts behind
them and their creators on [this
page](http://www.consumoresponsable.org/concursoconsumo/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=67&Itemid=16).

